ddObj.Name: cap_canBus_PT
ddObj.ddProperty: This struct represents the CAN bus PT. It collects the frames of the bus

ddObj.Name: PT_StateEcu01_1024_sts
ddObj.ddProperty: Representation of frame frame StateEcu01 (1024, 0x400) on bus PT plus transmission status

ddObj.Name: signals
ddObj.ddProperty: This field is a struct, which bundles all signals of frame frame StateEcu01 (1024, 0x400) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal checksum of frame frame StateEcu01 (1024, 0x400) on bus PT. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff Range (world values): 0.0 ... 255.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: speedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal speedOfRotation of frame frame StateEcu01 (1024, 0x400) on bus PT. Speed of rotation of the engine Range (world values): 0.0 ... 6500.0 [rpm]. Scaling: WorldValue = 0.1*BinaryValue + 0.0 [rpm]

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal sequenceCounter of frame frame StateEcu01 (1024, 0x400) on bus PT. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically increased counter value. The counter wraps around after 14 Range (world values): 0.0 ... 14.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: stsTransmission
ddObj.ddProperty: Transmission status of frame frame StateEcu01 (1024, 0x400) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: PT_StateEcu02_1040_sts
ddObj.ddProperty: Representation of frame frame StateEcu02 (1040, 0x410) on bus PT plus transmission status

ddObj.Name: signals
ddObj.ddProperty: This field is a struct, which bundles all signals of frame frame StateEcu02 (1040, 0x410) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal checksum of frame frame StateEcu02 (1040, 0x410) on bus PT. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff Range (world values): 0.0 ... 255.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal sequenceCounter of frame frame StateEcu02 (1040, 0x410) on bus PT. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically decreased counter value. The counter wraps around from 1 to 15 Range (world values): 15.0 ... 1.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: torque
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal torque of frame frame StateEcu02 (1040, 0x410) on bus PT. Current engine torque as estimated by the ECU Range (world values): -500.0 ... 500.0 [Nm]. Scaling: WorldValue = 0.5*BinaryValue + 0.0 [Nm]

ddObj.Name: stsTransmission
ddObj.ddProperty: Transmission status of frame frame StateEcu02 (1040, 0x410) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: PT_UserLimits_2032_sts
ddObj.ddProperty: Representation of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT plus transmission status

ddObj.Name: signals
ddObj.ddProperty: This field is a struct, which bundles all signals of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal sequenceCounter of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically increased counter value. The counter wraps around from 14 to 1 Range (world values): 1.0 ... 14.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: minSpeedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal minSpeedOfRotation of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT. User set minimum for speeed of rotation. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the speed falls below this limit Range (world values): 0.0 ... 6500.0 [rpm]. Scaling: WorldValue = 1.6*BinaryValue + 0.0 [rpm]

ddObj.Name: maxSpeedOfRotation
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal maxSpeedOfRotation of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT. User set maximum for speeed of rotation. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the limit is exceeded Range (world values): 0.0 ... 6500.0 [rpm]. Scaling: WorldValue = 1.6*BinaryValue + 0.0 [rpm]

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal checksum of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff Range (world values): 0.0 ... 255.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: minPower
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal minPower of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT. User set minimum for the engine power. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the power falls below this limit Range (world values): -10.0 ... 240.0 [KW]. Scaling: WorldValue = 0.5*BinaryValue + -10.0 [KW]

ddObj.Name: maxPower
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal maxPower of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT. User set maximum for the engine power. A CAN frame with according status bit is broadcasted by the supervising instance if the limit is exceeded Range (world values): -10.0 ... 240.0 [KW]. Scaling: WorldValue = 0.5*BinaryValue + -10.0 [KW]

ddObj.Name: stsTransmission
ddObj.ddProperty: Transmission status of frame frame UserLimits (2032, 0x7f0) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: signals
ddObj.ddProperty: This field is a struct, which bundles all signals of frame frame InfoPowerDisplay (1536, 0x600) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal checksum of frame frame InfoPowerDisplay (1536, 0x600) on bus PT. Message related checksum. The sum is defined such that the arithmetic sum of all message bytes (including the check sum itself) and the start value yields 0xff Range (world values): 0.0 ... 255.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal sequenceCounter of frame frame InfoPowerDisplay (1536, 0x600) on bus PT. Sequence counter of message origin. Each update of the message contents results in a cylically increased counter value. The counter wraps around after 14 Range (world values): 0.0 ... 14.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: power
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal power of frame frame InfoPowerDisplay (1536, 0x600) on bus PT. The computed, current output power of the engine The computed, current output power of the engine Range (world values): -500000.0 ... 500000.0 [W]. Scaling: WorldValue = 32.0*BinaryValue + -500000.0 [W]

ddObj.Name: state
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal state of frame frame InfoPowerDisplay (1536, 0x600) on bus PT. The status of the power computation. If the input information is invalid or suspicious or if there is an overflow in the computation then the computed power is unreliable. This status information will indicate whether the power information is reliabale or not and why not Range (world values): 0.0 ... 2.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: stsTransmission
ddObj.ddProperty: Transmission status of frame frame InfoPowerDisplay (1536, 0x600) on bus PT

ddObj.Name: noDlcErrors
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal noDlcErrors of frame frame StatusPowerDisplay (1537, 0x601) on bus PT. Number of recognized DLC errors in CAN input Range (world values): 0.0 ... 2047.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: noCheckSumErrors
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal noCheckSumErrors of frame frame StatusPowerDisplay (1537, 0x601) on bus PT. Number of recognized checksum errors in CAN input Range (world values): 0.0 ... 2047.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: noSqcErrors
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal noSqcErrors of frame frame StatusPowerDisplay (1537, 0x601) on bus PT. Number of recognized sequence errors in CAN input Range (world values): 0.0 ... 2047.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: sequenceCounter
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal sequenceCounter of frame frame StatusPowerDisplay (1537, 0x601) on bus PT. Sequence counter of message. The counter is incremented prior to sending the frame. The counter wraps around from 126 to 1. 0 and 127 are invalid values Range (world values): 1.0 ... 126.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: checksum
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal checksum of frame frame StatusPowerDisplay (1537, 0x601) on bus PT. Message related checksum. ddObj.ddProperty: Signal belowMinSpeedOfRotation of frame frame LimitsPowerDisplay (1538, 0x602) on bus PT. Boolean: True if and only if the speed of rotation is currently below the user set minimum Range (world values): 0.0 ... 1.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.ddProperty: Signal aboveMaxSpeedOfRotation of frame frame LimitsPowerDisplay (1538, 0x602) on bus PT. Boolean: True if and only if the speed of rotation is currently above the user set maximum Range (world values): 0.0 ... 1.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []

ddObj.Name: aboveMaxPower
ddObj.ddProperty: Signal aboveMaxPower of frame frame LimitsPowerDisplay (1538, 0x602) on bus PT. Boolean: True if and only if the engine power is currently above the user set maximum Range (world values): 0.0 ... 1.0 []. Scaling: WorldValue = BinaryValue []
